Amy Spanger (born 24 August 1971; age 52) is an actress from Newbury, Massachusetts who guest-starred on Law & Order: Special Victims Unit in the episode "PTSD" as Marlene Rosten, and in the episode "Great Expectations" as Helen Turner.

Spanger's television credits include: Ed, Becker, Egg: The Arts Show, Six Feet Under, Law And Order: SVU, Michael and Michael Have Issues, and Bored to Death. She also starred in the Showtime original movie musical Reefer Madness (2005) with Steven Weber, as the promiscuous Sally.

She appeared in Synecdoche, New York (2008) with Philip Seymour Hoffman and Dianne Wiest, written and directed by Charlie Kaufman.
